attachments.fallback:
Donald Miner commented on [medium] tcgplayer links to expensive version of the card sometimes. it should link to something a bit more reasonable.: "From Josh @ Tcgplayer

I noticed that on the links for each card the link for Card Kingdom uses a different set than the links for TCGplayer. This makes it so the displayed price can be a much smaller number than the price of the card that is being linked to. Lightning bolt is a good example:
<a alt="Buy at Card Kingdom" href="https://www.cardkingdom.com/mtg/4th-edition/lightning-bolt?partner=edhrec&utm_source=edhrec&utm_medium=affiliate&utm_campaign=edhrec" target="_blank" title="Buy at Card Kingdom">
<a alt="Buy at TCGplayer" href="https://store.tcgplayer.com/magic/alpha-edition/lightning-bolt?partner=EDHREC&utm_campaign=affiliate&utm_medium=EDHREC&utm_source=EDHREC" target="_blank" title="Buy at TCGplayer">

This means that Lightning Bolt is showing as $2.54 in price for the TCGplayer link but then it links to Alpha Lightning Bolt, priced at $279.95.

I reached out to the team here and there is another way that we can build the links if it's easier and you have productId tracked in your database: <https://shop.tcgplayer.com/product/productsearch?id=12345&partner=edhrec&utm_source=edhrec&utm_medium=affiliate&utm_campaign=edhrec>

If set names work better then I could put together a CSV that matches all of the sets up or something similar if you can get me a list of all of your sets, whatever makes it easiest. Or if you use the Scryfall sets I can get matching for that."
